{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["data"],"tokens":[{"text":"object ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SmartCard","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"properties","title":"Properties","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", the system disables smart cards for logins, authorizations, and screen saver unlocking. It’s still allowed for other functions, such as signing emails and accessing the web. The device requires a restart for a setting change to take effect."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"required":false,"name":"allowSmartCard","type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}],"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"true"}]},{"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Configures the certificate trust check and has one of the following possible values:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"text":": Turns off certificate trust check.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1"},{"text":": Turns on certificate trust check. The device performs a standard validity check but doesn’t include additional revocation checks.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2"},{"text":": Turns on certificate trust check. The device also performs a soft revocation check. Until CRL/OCSP explicitly rejects the certificate, the device considers it valid. This setting means that unavailable or unreachable CRL/OCSP allow this check to succeed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"3"},{"text":": Turns on certificate trust check. The device also performs a hard revocation check. Unless CRL/OCSP explicitly says “This certificate is OK,” the device considers it invalid. This option is the most secure.","type":"text"}]}]}]}],"type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}],"attributes":[{"value":"0","kind":"default"},{"values":["0","1","2","3"],"kind":"allowedValues"}],"required":false,"name":"checkCertificateTrust"},{"name":"enforceSmartCard","required":false,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", a user can only log in or authenticate with a smart card."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Available: macOS 10.13.2+"}]}],"attributes":[{"value":"false","kind":"default"}],"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","type":[{"text":"boolean","kind":"text"}]},{"type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}],"name":"oneCardPerUser","attributes":[{"kind":"default","value":"false"}],"required":false,"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":", a user can pair with only one smart card, although existing pairings are allowed if already set up."}]}]},{"required":false,"name":"tokenRemovalAction","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"code":"1","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the device enables the screen saver when the user removes the smart card.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Available: macOS 10.13.4+"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":[{"text":"integer","kind":"text"}],"attributes":[{"value":"0","kind":"default"},{"kind":"allowedValues","values":["0","1"]}],"introducedVersion":"10.12.4"},{"required":false,"introducedVersion":"10.12.4","attributes":[{"value":"true","kind":"default"}],"type":[{"kind":"text","text":"boolean"}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", users don’t get the pairing dialog, although existing pairings still work."}]}],"name":"UserPairing"}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Specify ","type":"text"},{"code":"com.apple.security.smartcard","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as the payload type."}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Profile-availability","type":"heading","text":"Profile availability"},{"type":"table","extendedData":{"0_1":{"colspan":0,"rowspan":1},"0_0":{"colspan":0,"rowspan":1}},"header":"row","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Device channel"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"User channel","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"N/A","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow manual install"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Requires supervision"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"N/A","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Requires user-approved MDM"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"N/A"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Allowed in user enrollment"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"N/A","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Allow multiple payloads"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"N/A"}]}]]]},{"type":"heading","text":"Profile example","anchor":"Profile-example","level":3},{"code":["<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>","<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC \"-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN\" \"http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd\">","<plist version=\"1.0\">","<dict